    <name>
				<text>23.6.2 Task 1a trig and Cartesian form</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
Write the following in \( \cos \theta + i\sin \theta \) form and Cartesian form. 
<ol class="HELM_parts_inline">
<li>\( e^{i\pi/6} = \cos\) [[input:ans1]] \( + i\sin \) [[input:ans2]]</li>
[[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]][[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]
<p></p>
<li>\( e^{i\pi/6} =\) [[input:ans3]] \( + \) [[input:ans4]]\(i\)</li>
[[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]][[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]]
<p></p>
Now write the following in \( \cos \theta + i\sin \theta \) form and Cartesian form. 
<p></p>
<li>\( e^{-i\pi/6} = \cos\) [[input:ans5]] \( + i\sin \) [[input:ans6]]</li>
[[validation:ans5]][[feedback:prt5]][[validation:ans6]][[feedback:prt6]]
<p></p>
<li>\( e^{-i\pi/6} =\) [[input:ans7]] \( + \) [[input:ans8]]\(i\)</li>
[[validation:ans7]][[feedback:prt7]][[validation:ans8]][[feedback:prt8]]
<p></p>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[We have by definition,
\[
\begin{align}
e^{i\pi/6} &amp;= \cos \left( \dfrac{\pi}{6} \right) + i \sin \left( \dfrac{\pi}{6} \right)  \\
&amp;= \displaystyle{@ta3@} + \displaystyle{@ta4@} i
\end{align}
 \]
and also
\[
\begin{align}
e^{-i\pi/6} &amp;= \cos \left( \dfrac{-\pi}{6} \right) + i \sin \left( \dfrac{-\pi}{6} \right)  \\
&amp;= \cos \left( \dfrac{\pi}{6} \right) - i \sin \left( \dfrac{\pi}{6} \right)  \\
&amp;= \displaystyle{@ta7@} - \dfrac{1}{2} i
\end{align}
 \]]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
